rules.ruleString: Must have passed 1 (I/W) units in {NUR2002, NUR2004, NUR3003, NUR3106}
Must be enrolled in course version {3953, 3963}

description: This unit addresses issues associated with transition to rural nursing practice and prepares students for the expanded generalist role that characterises rural nursing practice. Concerned with preparing students for a satisfying and sustainable rural nursing career, the unit requires students to explore opportunities for continuing education, professional affiliation and engagement and career advancement.
faculty: Faculty of Medicine, Nursing and Health Sciences
